@startuml Captraex_Website_EndToEnd_Sequence
title Captraex Website - Visitor Journey (Sign In + Checkout)
skinparam maxMessageSize 140
skinparam BoxPadding 10

legend top right
  **Risk Levels (Flows and Boundaries)**
  |<#White> Black Arrow | Internal / Low Risk |
  |<#FFE6CC> Orange Arrow | External Hand-off / Medium Risk |
  |<#FFCCCC> Red Arrow | High-Impact User-Trust Flow |
endlegend

box "External Visitor" #FFCCCC
actor Visitor as V
participant Browser as B
end box

box "Captraex Website Stack" #E6F2FF
participant "Captraex Website\n(Azure Static Web Apps)" as W
participant "Static Header Policy\n(staticwebapp.config.json)" as CFG
participant "GitHub Actions Deploy\n(Node 22 + next build)" as CI
end box

box "Captraex Services" #F2F9FF
participant "Product App\napp.captraex.com" as APP
participant "Public API\napi.captraex.com" as API
end box

box "Third-Party" #FFE6CC
participant "Stripe Hosted Checkout" as STRIPE
end box

== Deployment Path ==
CI -> W: Publish static export artifact
CI -> CFG: Apply global header policy

== Initial Visit ==
V -> B: Open https://captraex.com
B -> W: GET /, /features, /pricing
W -> CFG: Attach security headers + CSP
W --> B: HTML/CSS/JS response

== Preview Gate (when enabled) ==
B -> B: Check site-auth cookie\nand run client-side overlay logic
note right
  Gate is browser-side.
  No server-side auth boundary
  in current implementation.
end note

== Sign In Flow ==
V -[#orange]-> B: Click "Sign in"
B -[#orange]-> APP: HEAD / (pre-warm, no-cors)
B -[#orange]-> API: GET /health (pre-warm, no-cors)
B -[#red]-> APP: Navigate to /dashboard

== Trial Checkout Flow ==
V -[#orange]-> B: Click "Start trial"
B -[#orange]-> API: POST /api/subscription/checkout\n{target_tier, origin}
API -[#orange]-> STRIPE: Create checkout session
API -[#orange]-> B: Return { checkout_url }
B -[#red]-> STRIPE: Redirect to hosted checkout URL
@enduml
